lead_paragraph: Kim Clijsters lost her chance to reclaim the No. 1 ranking yesterday when she fell to Dinara Safina, 6-4, 7-6 (2), in the third round of the Italian Open in Rome. The second-ranked Clijsters would have moved past Amélie Mauresmo if she had won the title this week. Mauresmo was a late withdrawal because of illness.
